name: Hotel Grand Wijaya
address: Jl. Sudirman No.74, Banyuasri, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81116, Indonesia
review 1:
This is for the first time i stayed here,  first impression is the hospitality worth a 5 star hotel. The room is clean, is a semi traditional modern hotel.

Although the parking area was small, but the staff very kind to direct our car to a good spot.

And this hotel give you a room for smoking and chilling with spirits of course.

Very Good,
review 2: With cottage-style concept, the room and environtment is large. The service is very nice and the crew is very polite and helpful. Food is standard. You can do laundry here. This hotel suits you if you plan to stay long time
review 3: the room is okay, but a bit scary, the tv can't be turned on, the remote tv doesn't work, the air conditioner is hard to turn down, I often come here, but today I'm disappointed, please improve
review 4:
The hotel offers nice and clean bedroom bathroom with hot cold shower, no bath (but we dont need one). I love the cottage style room with big terrace. They don't have cable TV - although guests won't stay in the room for long - but I think it's nice to have one. The staffs are really nice and friendly, treat us well so we feel comfortable here.
I think this is the best budget hotel in the middle of Singaraja.
review 5: We got a single room bungalow. Room a bit smaller than other room, though the rate is higher. Very calm place in the middle of Singaraja area. We have checked other rooms, cheper rooms are in the main building, but bit dark some has no real windows. Overall, this is a good option for staying in Singaraja. Good price and staff are very friendly and helpful.

name: Mie Kober
address: Jl. Dewi Sartika Utara No.34, Kaliuntu, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81116, Indonesia
review 1: This place selling noodle with a varition taste of spicy noodle. There are a lot of dumplings too here and many kind of drink. The noodle is very delicious and because I love spicy food, the spicy noodle here are very good. If you dont like a spicy food like my wife, you can also order not spicy noodle or other kind food. Here selling sushi and fried rice too. For the place, you can eat here or bring home and the waiters will call your name if your order is done.
review 2: Good service, place is clean & chic. Fast order for noodles & dimsum but not for rice. Nice ambience for dine-in at 2nd floor. 1st floor for take out & order.
review 3:
The chicken katsu, karage & chicken wing are dissapointed me. The chicken katsu and karage are not served warmly and they are tasteless.
I ordered spicy chicken wing as well but it was not spicy at all and the meat is not fresh
review 4: A neat eatery a lot of student types kitchen is made from a forty foot container good menu great prices
review 5:
I love to eat here, the variety is very good, food is tasty and the prices are great.
This is a popular place for locals to eat

name: New Garuda Hotel
address: Jl. A. Yani No.76, Kaliuntu, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81116, Indonesia
review 1: Room and Bed was bad and dusty, dirty stained bed and bed SMELLS VERY BAD!!! Aircon not cool. TV not working. Hot water unavailable. Unfriendly staff. Shame on OYO Brand for cleanliness and comfort. My son was badly allergic with dust. Please review the Hotel condition regularly so it won't mislead what had been advertised. Very NOT HAPPY AT ALL.
review 2:
We were in this town for a visit, and it was a bit late to travel back home. I booked this place from OYO, and it was really fast booking.

Besides of the good deal we have from OYO application, the check in process was easy and fast. Receptionist was friendly and helpful.

Room itself is OK for a family with 2 kids. We had 1 king size bed and 1 single. Perfect for us. Room was clean. Got 2 bottles of complimentary water. By the way, they said if you booked from OYO app, we won't get breakfast though.

Aircon was cold, hot shower is available, flatscreen TV and it had usb plug if you want to watch your own movie from a flash drive or external drive.

Bathroom is pretty standard, It's a bit small for a big room. Also, they didn't give us bath soap, don't know if they forgot.

Anyway, we enjoyed our stay there. Good place for a very good price in the middle of town. You  can walk around the area to get groceries and other things pretty easily.
review 3: Okay, here's the bottom line. You are an explorer without deep pockets, riding all over Bali for adventure and fun, and you just need a cozy bed to sleep before you head out again in the morning. This hotel serves that exact purpose. Dont bother caring about cleanliness, or even hot water for that matter (as we didn't have hot water,) but the beds are cozy and it gets the job done at rock bottom prices. Noteworthy mention, you do get a free toothbrush. Hey... Real life means often "roughing it," so you get what you pay for. Good luck. Oh and, there is great nasi goreng and other bargain, delicious foods in the neighborhood if you venture out and walk at night.
review 4:
Good place for stay on Singaraja, near to everyplace on Singaraja.
But for water heater is not good, sometime it works sometimes it not work.
Please fix it. Have different price if you book on online and on the spot
review 5: Was about to give it 3 stars but decided to give it 1 star after i found A USED CONDOM outside our window. Easily the most disgusting hotel I‚Äôve ever stayed in. The sheets floor and walls are so dirty.

review 1: Super delicious and affordable, especially Mie Ayam. I think they serve one of the best Mie Ayam in the city. review 3: Came here after leaving Singaraja for quite long. I am surprised with the taste, it‚Äôs so tasty and the price is so affordable! It would be one of the things I‚Äôll miss about Singaraja üòã‚ù§Ô∏è
review 4: The meatballs are fresh and delicious. They have quite so many varians. Meatball lovers will love this place
review 5: Pleasantly surprised by quality and prices. Three of us had different meals and all said they were great. Will go again for sure.

name: Burger Bangor Express 86
address: V3PJ+42M, Jl. A. Yani, Banyuasri, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: The burgers are great. The place is not really. There is not enough parking place because it is directly beside the road. The service is so so. There is only transfer option for cashless which is more complicated than qris. The pegawai are not too friendlly. And it takes too long for a burger and a french fries. They need to work quickly.
review 2:
The place is easy to access, the parking areas is suit for motorcycle and if you bring a car, its so hard to parking in the front of it.

Not recommended for dine in, because there 's only 2 tables inside.

i bought 2 sultan and 1 fish, its so so
review 3:
Management...guys...please..
Visit your business..
See what your staff are doing to your investment..
This is a franchise I presume and unfortunately my experience was far less than desirable.
And I  see by the number of poor ratings other customers agree with me.
The location is great,  very central and easy parking available in the front of the shop.
Inside is very small,  best suited for takeaway rather than dine in as I did.
There are only 2 tables and a few chairs for customers to sit on while waiting.
Inside first impressions.
Dirty.
Untidy.
Overstaffed.
Music incredibly loud.
We ordered 2 x Sultan burgers which are the pride of the business.
But it was horribly underwhelming with only 2 meat patties  and not 3 (staff obviously cannot count)
2 x portions of fries that were absolutely drenched in topping!!
Would I come back again?
Most Definitely Not...
I don't recommend anyone else to come here, there are better experiences in Singaraga.
review 4: I won't go back there. Meat, fries and the beef had nothing special
review 5: Avoid the fish burger, it looked old and fried to death, even McDonald's poorest Fishmac is 10x better. Their Sultan Burger was OK though. The service was good and fast.

name: Martabak Pecenongan 78, Singaraja
address: V3PJ+43V, Banyuasri, Buleleng, Buleleng Regency, Bali 81116, Indonesia
review 1:
Martabak is of course famous Street food across Indonesia.
This company have moved the street food inside a clean spacious shop.
It's easy to find.
Plenty of carparking available outside the door.
Service was prompt.
Seating while waiting was a bit limited
But...
What is the food like.
Its great!!!
The sweet martabak is superior to any local ones I've tried.
The egg martabak is only the same as the local ones available in the area.
Prices are more than local prices
But the sweet martabak is definitely worth it!!
Would I come back again?
Probably!
review 2: The real delicious taste, no a la a la

Great idea.

Would I come back again?
Yes of course!!
review 2: Winners Cafe and Carwash offers a unique experience where you can enjoy tasty food while waiting for your car to be washed. The cafe's menu is impressive, with delicious options. However, the car wash service could use some improvement. The wait time for the car wash is longer than expected, which can be a bit inconvenient.
review 3: I came here for washing my car, not cheap and the result kind a disappointed for me, I still can find breads crumbs easily at interior, and stain all over windshield
